      <p>The data was acquired using a Neurofax EEG-1200 system at a sampling rate of 2,000 Hz. The electrical stimulus consisted of a constant current square wave pulse of 0.3 ms duration, the current intensity of 5 mA, and the pulse frequency of 1 Hz with alternative polarity. About fifty biphasic pulses of electrical stimulation were delivered to two neighboring contacts in each session, while the EEG signals of all electrode contacts were recorded.</p>
